tags: Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
context: Pre and Post Delivery Care,Caesarean Section (C Section),
review:
Dr Shilpa Abhyankar came highly recommended from my family physician for my first preganancy. The preganancy itself was challenging as I had to be on complete bed rest for 9 months. Dr Shilpa has been a firm, asseritive and strong guide through this journey. She has been extremely involved and  meticulous with respect to scans and ensuring that me and the baby were safe. I  had an  episode of bleeding for which she was present even at 4 am. She made arrangements for premature delivery and NICU if need be. Close to my due date I found the fetal movements to be lesser. She was prompt in asking me to do a scan and planned for an emergency c section and which was the best decision! Even post the delivery she was involved and concerned about the baby as well as my health. The post natal checksups and guidance were very helpful.
All in all, I could not have asked for a more knowledgeable, meticulous and concerned gynecologist for my first preganancy.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: I had been under Dr. Shilpa's treatment from the very beginning of my pregnancy and I delivered my baby at Parchure Nursing home. Her judgements were always very accurate which helped us in making the right decisions at right time. The staff of Parchure Nursing home is well trained and very helping. The atmosphere was very homely and comforting, following all the necessary precautions, especially in the view of Covid. In spite of my gestational diabetes, I had a wonderful experience of pregnancy, delivery and speedy recovery post delivery. I had complete faith in Dr. Shilpa which helped me stay calm. I would recommend her not only for her expertise but also for the genuine concern and care that she has for her patients.

review: Sharing feedback basis the entire 9 months pregnancy journey and delivery at Dr Shilpa's nursing home.Dr Shilpa was extremely patient.. really took the time to address our concerns and explain things in detail. She also patiently attended the concerns/ doubts of our family members She is highly experienced and we could trust her at ecah step. She always kept us in loop about the process/ next steps.Delivery experience at the nursing home was also very smooth. Dr frequently attended me and monitored the progress. Pushed and encouraged to recover faster. The delivery cost was reasonable. The staff was friendly, involved and hands on. Lastly, hygiene level at the clinic were well maintained and necessary covid protocols were strictly followed at all timesGrateful that we chose Dr Shilpa for this milestone of our life. Would highly recommend her.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,
review:
Since we're in a pandemic, I set up an online appointment with the doctor to discuss my history and ask about necessary tests before I could make an in-person appointment. This was my experience online:

1. The doctor ignored my indicted preference for a video call.
2. The doctor rushed through the entire call, barely asking me 3-4 questions. I had to go out of my way to offer up information.
3. The doctor did not want to discuss my history when she heard that I would want to come in for an in-person appointment for the actual examination (not caring for the money I had already spent).  
4. She made no attempt to offer any comfort or context when I disclosed what was ailing me. 

I fully understand that the consultation had to be limited until the actual examination and I made that clear. However, I paid to discuss symptoms and get more information about who might be diagnosing and treating me. *** ****** ********** ** ***
